You can use the `FileSaver.js` library to save text to a local file in a browser. Here's an example code snippet:


```javascript
// first, include the FileSaver.js script from https://github.com/eligrey/FileSaver.js/blob/master/dist/FileSaver.min.js or use a CDN link
const textToSave = 'Hello World!';
const fileName = 'hello.txt';

function saveTextAsFile() {
  const fileToSave = new Blob([textToSave], { type: 'text/plain' });
  FileSaver.saveAs(fileToSave, fileName);
}
```

This will create a `hello.txt` file with the text "Hello World!" in it and prompt the user to save it to their computer.

Note that this method requires the user's browser to support the FileSaver API, which may not work on older browsers or mobile devices.
